{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04748/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04748"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:47:48"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["extreme close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["high"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}}],"summary":{"none":["An embroidered rose with a needle puncturing the fabric."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04748/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04748","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04748/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04748"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04748/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04748/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04748/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04748/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04748/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04748/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04748/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04748/canvas/1/d9ce9d5d-d1d1-4f98-bc86-54cab9608a66","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T19:05:56.270Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The first shot of Alma’s cross-stitching features the needle piercing the fabric from below. <em>Phantom Thread</em>, in one sense, is the story of Alma rising from the bottom and taking her place in Reynolds’s House of Woodcock. This trajectory is seen in shots at his London home in which the characters trade places on the long, winding staircase. Here, the needle might be seen as Alma herself—a muse and a stubborn woman who can pierce Reynolds’s outer shell.&nbsp;</p><p>Similarly, she weaves herself into Reynolds’ life like the thread.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04748/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:747.4575332348589,651.2647710487452,447.54200516986714,216.26200147710495"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04748/canvas/1/5f39d6de-7111-4004-b098-019035b918e1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T19:06:09.969Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The colors present in Alma’s design are red and green: the two colors with which she is associated through her <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW94671690 BCX0\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-01247.html\"><u>red</u></a> and <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW94671690 BCX0\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-04039.html\"><u>green</u></a> dresses and <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW94671690 BCX0\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-04733.html\"><u>green</u></a> shirt.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04748/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:621.9405465288029,241.75590841949852,638.0123707533236,381.923929098966"}}}]}]}]}